<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTEHarold_G._Coward19903–12,_36–47,_111–112,_Note:_Sanskrit_was_both_a_literary_and_spoken_language_in_ancient_India.-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHarold_G._Coward19903–12,_36–47,_111–112,_Note:_Sanskrit_was_both_a_literary_and_spoken_language_in_ancient_India._10-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEHarold_G._Coward19903–12,_36–47,_111–112,_Note:_Sanskrit_was_both_a_literary_and_spoken_language_in_ancient_India._10-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFHarold_G._Coward1990">Harold G. Coward 1990</a>, pp.&#160;3–12, 36–47, 111–112, Note: Sanskrit was both a literary and spoken language in ancient India..</span>
