<li id="cite_note-Woolner1986p3-26"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Woolner1986p3_26-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Woolner1986p3_26-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFAlfred_C._Woolner1986" class="citation book">Alfred C. Woolner (1986). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=IwE16UFBfdEC"><i>Introduction to Prakrit</i></a>. Motilal Banarsidass. pp.&#160;3–4. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-81-208-0189-9" title="Special:BookSources/978-81-208-0189-9"><bdi>978-81-208-0189-9</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Introduction+to+Prakrit&amp;rft.pages=3-4&amp;rft.pub=Motilal+Banarsidass&amp;rft.date=1986&amp;rft.isbn=978-81-208-0189-9&amp;rft.au=Alfred+C.+Woolner&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DIwE16UFBfdEC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASanskrit" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/>, Quote:"If in 'Sanskrit' we include the Vedic language and all dialects of the Old Indian period, then it is true to say that all the Prakrits are derived from Sanskrit. If on the other hand 'Sanskrit' is used more strictly of the Panini-Patanjali language or 'Classical Sanskrit,' then it is untrue to say that any Prakrit is derived from Sanskrit, except that Sauraseni, the Midland Prakrit, is derived from the Old Indian dialect of the Madhyadesa on which Classical Sanskrit was mainly based."</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Bright2014p16-27"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Bright2014p16_27-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Bright2014p16_27-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFWilliam_Bright2014" class="citation book">William Bright (2014). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=TVa1BwAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA16"><i>American Indian Linguistics and Literature</i></a>. Walter De Gruyter. pp.&#160;16–17. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-3-11-086311-6" title="Special:BookSources/978-3-11-086311-6"><bdi>978-3-11-086311-6</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=American+Indian+Linguistics+and+Literature&amp;rft.pages=16-17&amp;rft.pub=Walter+De+Gruyter&amp;rft.date=2014&amp;rft.isbn=978-3-11-086311-6&amp;rft.au=William+Bright&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DTVa1BwAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPA16&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASanskrit" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
