<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTESalomon199892,_Quote:_&quot;Finally,_after_this_transitional_period_in_the_fourth_and_early_fifth_centuries_AD,_Prakrit_fell_out_of_use_completely_in_southern_Indian_inscriptions._For_the_next_few_centuries_Sanskrit_was_the_sole_epigraphic_language,_until_the_regional_Dravidian_languages_began_to_come_into_use_around_the_seventh_century&quot;.-331"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTESalomon199892,_Quote:_&quot;Finally,_after_this_transitional_period_in_the_fourth_and_early_fifth_centuries_AD,_Prakrit_fell_out_of_use_completely_in_southern_Indian_inscriptions._For_the_next_few_centuries_Sanskrit_was_the_sole_epigraphic_language,_until_the_regional_Dravidian_languages_began_to_come_into_use_around_the_seventh_century&quot;._331-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFSalomon1998">Salomon 1998</a>, p.&#160;92, Quote: "Finally, after this transitional period in the fourth and early fifth centuries AD, Prakrit fell out of use completely in southern Indian inscriptions. For the next few centuries Sanskrit was the sole epigraphic language, until the regional Dravidian languages began to come into use around the seventh century"..<span class="error harv-error" style="display: none; font-size:100%"> sfn error: multiple targets (3×): CITEREFSalomon1998 (<a href="/wiki/Category:Harv_and_Sfn_template_errors" title="Category:Harv and Sfn template errors">help</a>)</span></span>
